                  <h1>Requirements</h1>
                  <p>Our standards are extremely high &ndash; but so too are the rewards. 
                    These are our requirements at the various levels:</p>
                  <h2 class="questions">Analyst</h2>
                  <ul>
                    <li>The minimum requirement is usually a 2:1 degree or equivalent 
                      (either achieved or realistically expected).</li>
                    <li>Specific languages are required for some roles.</li>
                    <li>Any degree discipline is usually acceptable &ndash; check individual 
                      job descriptions for exceptions.</li>
                    <li>Summer internships are designed for students in their 
                      penultimate year of study only.</li>
                    <li>Full-time graduate opportunities are designed for students 
                      who are graduating in the summer or who have graduated in 
                      the last year.</li>
                    <li>Candidates must demonstrate a combination of academic 
                      aptitude, quantitative skills, strategic and creative thinking, 
                      and written and oral communications skills.</li>
                  </ul>
                  <h2 class="questions">MBA positions</h2>
                  <ul>
                    <li>You must have an MBA or other advanced degree from a top-tier 
                      business school.</li>
                    <li>You will need a track record of superior performance in 
                      extracurricular and professional activities.</li>
                    <li>For summer internships, you must be in your penultimate 
                      year of study.</li>
                  </ul>
                  <h2 class="questions">PhD positions</h2>
                  <ul>
                    <li>An advanced degree/PhD in a mathematical or financial 
                      discipline is required.</li>
                  </ul>
                  <h2 class="questions">Europe Card Services</h2>
                  <ul>
                    <li>You must have obtained, or are realistically expecting 
                      to obtain, a minimum 2:2 degree or equivalent in a discipline 
                      directly relating to the stream you apply for (this varies).</li>
                    <li>We look for graduates who demonstrate a combination of 
                      academic aptitude, strategic and creative thinking, and 
                      strong written and oral communication skills.</li>
                    <li>You should be dedicated to a career in an environment 
                      that is highly commercial and focused on excellent customer 
                      service.</li>
                  </ul>
